Grind the fennel seeds.Mix with finely chopped fennel, apple, sage, lemon and lemon juice.Add oil, salt and freshly ground black pepper.Heat the oil. Add the wedges of aubergine.Cook slowly, approximately four minutes.Place the cubed potatoes into a pan of boiling water and cook until soft, approximately eight minutes, and drain.Add chilli, garlic and onion to the aubergine, cook for three minutes and take off the heat. Place the hot potatoes in a mixing bowl with the vinegar, olive oil, basil and squashed cherry tomatoes. Pour over the aubergines and their juices. Mix.Grill the pork on both sides and then roast at 180C/350F/Gas 4 for ten minutes with the lemons.Serve with the salsa and the warm salad.